PROPERTY: Microstructure_extracted: The microstructure of the CrNbTiVZr alloy sample after 50% compression deformation at 1273 K shows surface bulging, with the bottom side deforming more extensively than the top part, likely due to a temperature gradient. Characteristic bands at grain boundaries and inside the grains are formed, consisting of fine, recrystallized grains with a fine duplex structure of second-phase precipitates and transformed matrix. The second-phase particles become larger and their volume fraction increases compared to the non-deformed sample. Both the matrix and second-phase particles have BCC crystal structures, with the particles having the same crystallographic orientations as the respective matrix grains.
